cern philosophy today. With the benefit of this fuller picture of his thought, Merleau-Ponty and Contemporary Philosophy undertakes an assessment of the philosopher's relevance for contemporary thinking. Covering a diverse range of topics, including ontology, epistemology, anthropology, embodiment, animality, politics, language, aesthetics, and art, the editors gather representative voices from North America and Europe, including both Merleau-Ponty specialists and thinkers who have come to the philosopher's work through their own thematic interest.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aPhilosophy : Aesthetics. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Phenomenology.2bisacsh1 aAhmed, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlloa, Emmanuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlloa, Emmanuel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBarbaras, Renaud, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenoist, Jocelyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarbone, Mauro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChouraqui, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChouraqui, Frank, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDufourcq, Annabelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlynn, Bernard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFóti, Véronique M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiuliani, Regula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Galen A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaushik, Ra